Consolidated Edison Inc. (ED)  agreed to
acquire stakes in two solar farms that  Sempra Energy (SRE)  is building
in Nevada and Arizona.  The two companies will each own 50 percent of the 150-megawatt Copper Mountain 2 project near Las Vegas and the 150-megawatt Mesquite Solar 1 power plant near Phoenix, San Diego-based Sempra said in a statement today. Terms werenâ€™t disclosed.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
